        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 11:27PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 1126 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northwest of Niles, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Solomon, Niles, Talmage, Manchester, and Abilene.

This includes Interstate 70 between mile markers 267 and 273.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
